## The Workflow Pattern: Spec → Plan → Beads → Dispatch

For ANY significant work (features, projects, integrations), use the GT Toolkit workflow formulas. This ensures dependencies are wired correctly, preventing CPU overload from uncontrolled parallelism.

### The Full Pipeline

```bash
# 1. Spec: Idea → Reviewed design spec
gt sling spec-workflow crew/<agent> \
  --var feature="my-feature" \
  --var brief="One sentence describing what to build"

# 2. Plan: Spec → Phased implementation plan
gt sling plan-workflow crew/<agent> \
  --var feature="my-feature"

# 3. Beads: Plan → Issue hierarchy with dependencies
gt sling beads-workflow crew/<agent> \
  --var feature="my-feature"

# 4. Dispatch: Controlled by dependencies
gt sling <bead-id> <rig>
```

### Why This Pattern

| Step | CPU Control |
|------|-------------|
| **Spec** | Design decisions made upfront — no rework |
| **Plan** | Phased delivery — natural serialization |
| **Beads** | Dependencies wired — enforces ordering |
| **Dispatch** | `bd dep` blocks prevent parallel expensive work |

### For Projects (Multi-Rig)

Use `spec-project-workflow` for cross-rig projects:

```bash
gt sling spec-project-workflow crew/<agent> \
  --var feature="my-project" \
  --var brief="One sentence" \
  --var primary_rig="sfgastown" \
  --var rigs="sfgastown,lora_forge"
```

This includes Step 9.5 (bv robot triage) — quality gate before dispatch.

### One-Off Tasks: Use `gt block`

For tasks outside the workflow (quick fixes, experiments):

```bash
bd create "Quick fix" --type=task
gt sling <task-id> <rig>
```

If the task is expensive (tests, builds, training), make it exclusive:

```bash
gt block <task-id>  # Blocks all other ready work
```

### Anti-Patterns to Avoid

| Pattern | Problem | Fix |
|---------|---------|-----|
| `bd create "Do the thing"` → `gt sling` | No dependencies, uncontrolled parallelism | Use workflow formulas |
| Filing 10 tasks, slinging all at once | CPU overload | Wire deps: `bd dep add` |
| Skipping spec/plan, going straight to beads | Missing design decisions, rework | Run spec-workflow first |

